  "read": [
    "EP8 keeps owner-rank VJP math smaller than EP4, but the backward combine tail gets worse: combine_dx median is 25.12 ms/call on EP8 versus 14.74 ms/call on EP4, with EP8 p90 at 64.53 ms.",
    "EP4 local owner VJP math is heavier because each owner rank owns more experts: local_vjp.padded median is 45.44 ms/call on EP4 versus 29.63 ms/call on EP8.",
    "The kernel-family view shows three large non-loss buckets to pursue: ROCm GEMM kernels, MORI combine, and attention fwd/bwd kernels. At EP8 the rank-median kernel totals are 2.83 s GEMM, 2.38 s MORI combine, and 2.10 s attention fwd/bwd inside the profiled step.",
    "The dense linear backward labels split the MmBackward0 bucket: shared expert backward is about 2.0 s rank-median on both EP4 and EP8, attention projection backward is only about 0.21-0.22 s, and router gate backward is negligible. The raw profiled-linear CPU span is much larger because it includes nested/waiting behavior and should not be read as GPU GEMM time.",
    "Loss/lm-head chunk forward is a separate large loss-side dense-work bucket in the profiler: 14.63 s rank-median on EP4 and 20.06 s on EP8. Keep it separate from attention/MoE optimization decisions until we inspect whether the canary loss path is doing extra full-vocab chunk work that final training should shard or fuse.",
    "Next MoE work should not be another blind MORI launch tuple sweep. EP8 needs split/overlapped backward combine or MORI-native overlap; EP4/EP8 both still need a fused owner-rank MoE backward that reduces the padded VJP GEMM/recompute stack."
